com.ucsf.core.data

Class SharedTables.Sensors

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ucsf.core.data.SharedTables.Sensors
  • Enclosing class:
    SharedTables

    public abstract static class SharedTables.Sensors
extends java.lang.Object
    Table storing data coming from the patient's watch sensors. The same table definition can be use for other Android devices. Fields are:
    - DataManager.KEY_TIMESTAMP [TEXT] : Time of the acquisition
    - DataManager.KEY_PATIENT_ID [TEXT] : Unique id of the patient
    - DataManager.KEY_IS_COMMITTED [BOOLEAN]: Indicates if the entry has been synchronized with a remote device
    - KEY_ACC_X [REAL] : X component of the device acceleration
    - KEY_ACC_Y [REAL] : Y component of the device acceleration
    - KEY_ACC_Z [REAL] : Z component of the device acceleration
    - KEY_AZIMUTH [REAL] : Azimuth component of the device orientation
    - KEY_PITCH [REAL] : Pitch component of the device orientation
    - KEY_ROLL [REAL] : roll component of the device orientation
    - KEY_HEART_RATE [REAL] : Heart rate of the user. Not supported.
    - KEY_IS_HEART_RATE_VALID[BOOLEAN]: Indicates if the heart rate data are valid
    - KEY_STEP_COUNT [INTEGER]: Number of steps since the last entry
